					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Obligatory link to <a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/8x8s.png" class="postlink">8x8 fonts ripped from various games</a>
<br />
<br />Fonts <em>can</em> be design-patented in the United States and elsewhere. But this is rare, and in any case, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:PD#Fonts" class="postlink">it expires within 20 to 25 years</a>, long enough that any exclusive rights in fonts from the NES's commercial era (as well as Apple Chicago, the basis for the "who's cuter" font shown in my rip pic) will have expired.</div>

					
							<br /><br />
